</emphasis>
Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3286529FFB6FFD9FF6872DF36B0FC97" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB6FFDAFF6872DF3088F80D" blockId="1.[151,1436,1928,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB6FFDAFF6872DF3474F842" bold="true" box="[197,352,1928,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Description.</emphasis>
Adult Female. Head. Eyes bare, widely separated as wide as 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFBE172DE317EF843" box="[1100,1130,1929,1955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="13.0">13</number>
facets. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB6FFDAFA9072DE3086F843" box="[1341,1426,1929,1955]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFADB72DE3096F843" box="[1398,1410,1929,1955]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
a
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFF7B72F935F1F828" box="[214,229,1966,1992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
basal and 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFEC772F9346DF828" box="[362,377,1966,1992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
lateral setae. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB6FFDAFD3272F937ECF828" box="[671,760,1966,1992]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFD7772F937F1F828" box="[730,741,1966,1992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="1.0">1</number>
b
</figureCitation>
) brown, flagellomeres I–X vessel like with lateral and middle setae, flagellomere XI elongate, with many dorsal and one stiff apical setae; AR (Antennal ratio) 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB6FFDAFACC7284308CF80D" box="[1377,1432,2003,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="1.06">1.06</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF3A75CF35E8FF1C" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Maxillary palpus (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FED675CF34C6FF52" box="[379,466,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FE1B75CF34D6FF52" box="[438,450,152,178]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
c
</figureCitation>
) brown; palpal segment III dark brown moderately swollen at midlength with sensory pit, palpomere IV+V pale brown, with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FD6E75EA37C6FF37" box="[707,722,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="4.0">4</number>
apical setae; PR (Palpal ratio) 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FB9275EA3162FF37" box="[1087,1142,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="2.33">2.33</number>
. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FAAF75EA3042FF37" box="[1282,1366,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FA9475EA3050FF37" box="[1337,1348,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
d
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FF3A75B535A0FF1C" box="[151,180,226,252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="12.0">12</number>
teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF68745F36D3FEC2" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" box="[197,967,264,290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Thorax. Brown. Scutum with anterolateral and caudolateral setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF68747A3401FE72" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FEBB747A347EFEA7" box="[278,362,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FEE0747A344DFEA7" box="[333,345,301,327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
e
</figureCitation>
). Length = 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FE58747A373FFEA7" box="[501,555,301,327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.71">0.71</number>
, breadth = 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FD1D747A37F3FEA7" box="[688,743,301,327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.37">0.37</number>
; CR (Costal ratio) = 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FC73747A3101FEA7" box="[990,1045,301,327]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.52">0.52</number>
. Hyaline, with brown stigma and anterior veins; surface with dense microtrichia. Costa with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FC25740536C2FE8C" box="[904,982,338,364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="28.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="26.0">26–30</number>
setae. Radial cell ill developed. An bifurcated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF6874CA3469FDC7" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Legs. Brown. Fore tarsomeres I and II yellowish, III and IV brown; mid tarsomeres I with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FA8374CA3029FE57" box="[1326,1341,413,439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
basal 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FA2074CA3088FE57" box="[1421,1436,413,439]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
medial 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FF42749535EAFE3C" box="[239,254,450,476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
apical setae, II with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FE5B74953711FE3C" box="[502,517,450,476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
apical seta; hind tarsomeres I with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FC07749536ADFE3C" box="[938,953,450,476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="2.0">2</number>
basal and 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FB9574953153FE3C" box="[1080,1095,450,476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
apical setae, II with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FA927495305AFE3C" box="[1343,1358,450,476]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
apical seta. 
<collectingCountry id="F3257632FFB5FFD9FF7B74BF3406FDE2" box="[214,274,488,514]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial comb (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FE1A74BF371EFDE2" box="[439,522,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FE5C74BF34E8FDE2" box="[497,508,488,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
f
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FDF674BF377EFDE2" box="[603,618,488,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
unequal setae and pointed spur. 
<collectingCountry id="F3257632FFB5FFD9FC5674BF3135FDE2" box="[1019,1057,488,514]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">TR</collectingCountry>
(Tarsal ratio) of hind leg 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FAF274BF308CFDE2" box="[1375,1432,488,514]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.41">1.41</number>
. Claws small, equal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF68776536EEFD92" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Abdomen. Tergites Yellowish brown. Spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FCEF7765368CFDAC" box="[834,920,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CCA9B47FFB5FFD9FCD67765368CFDAC" box="[891,920,562,588]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized unequal, oval to sub oval 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FF3A770F35CDFD92" box="[151,217,600,626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.048">0.048</number>
x 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FF5B770F342CFD92" box="[246,312,600,626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.027">0.027</number>
and 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FEDC770F34A7FD92" box="[369,435,600,626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.038">0.038</number>
x 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FE7D770F3706FD92" box="[464,530,600,626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.023">0.023</number>
with small neck and 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FCA1770F360FFD92" box="[780,795,600,626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
small apical spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF68772A36B0FC97" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FF68772A344EFD77" bold="true" box="[197,346,637,663]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Adult Male.</emphasis>
Similar to female, with typical sexual differences. Wing brown with pale stigma and anterior veins, microtrichia densely covering wing surface. Legs grayish. Wing length 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FBFC77F5319DFD5C" box="[1105,1161,674,700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.67">0.67</number>
, breadth 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FB5477F53036FD5C" box="[1273,1314,674,700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.3">0.3</number>
, CR 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FACD77F5308DFD5C" box="[1376,1433,674,700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="0.46">0.46</number>
. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13092A27FFB5FFD9FEB9779F347FFD02" box="[276,363,712,738]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 a – h" captionStartId="1.[151,270,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[253,1347,636,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[224,1363,608,1821]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 a – h. Leptoconops (Holoconops) brevistylus sp. n. Female: a: clypeus, b: antenna, c: maxillary palpus, d: mandible, e: wing, f: hind tibial comb, g: spermatheca, h: male genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198055/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FEE6779F3443FD02" box="[331,343,712,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
h
</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX nearly as long as broad, lateral margin thickened, median process of posterior margin extremely long with slender. Gonocoxite long, with few dorsal (
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FB8077BA314BFCE7" box="[1069,1119,749,775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
) setae; gonostylus short, attenuated to abrupt point bearing 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FD9B76453751FCCC" box="[566,581,786,812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="3.0">3</number>
dorsal and 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FD7F764537F5FCCC" box="[722,737,786,812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="1.0">1</number>
stout subapical setae, tip sometimes prolonged in form of lamelliform expansion at its ventral margin; aedeagus long nipple like; parameres well sclerotized, elongate, with truncated base bearing incurved subapical fang-like structure.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3286529FFB5FFD9FF6876D53624FB27" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D36A2FFB5FFD9FF6876D53624FB27" blockId="2.[151,1438,152,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FF6876D53444FC7C" bold="true" box="[197,336,898,924]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">Discussion.</emphasis>
The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FE4A76D53601FC7C" authority="Carter" authorityName="Carter" box="[487,789,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus" subGenus="Holoconops">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FE4A76D537D1FC7B" box="[487,709,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">L. (H.) americanus</emphasis>
Carter
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FCE376D531FFFC7C" authority="Clastrier &amp; Wirth" authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Wirth" box="[846,1259,898,924]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knowltoni" subGenus="Holoconops">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FCE376D53102FC7B" box="[846,1046,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">L. (H.) knowltoni</emphasis>
Clastrier &amp; Wirth
</taxonomicName>
come closer to the new species in structure of gonocoxite, gonostylus and setae on flagellomeres. Palpomere III with its sensory pit looks like that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FE5C769A36ABFC07" authority="Clastrier &amp; Wirth. In" authorityName="Clastrier &amp; Wirth. In" box="[497,959,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni" subGenus="Holoconops">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FE5C769A37ABFC06" box="[497,703,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">L. (H.) andersoni</emphasis>
Clastrier &amp; Wirth. In
</taxonomicName>
the wing venation, setae of femora, and structure of the stigma and spermatheca, the present species shows similarities with those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FAE376A537C8FBD2" authority="Chanthawanich &amp; Delfinado" authorityName="Chanthawanich &amp; Delfinado" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplifemoralis" subGenus="Holoconops">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FAE376A53448FBD1" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">L.(H.) amplifemoralis</emphasis>
Chanthawanich &amp; Delfinado
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FCB0714F3162FBD2" authority="Ma &amp; Yu" authorityName="Ma &amp; Yu" box="[797,1142,1048,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helobius" subGenus="Holoconops">
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FCB0714F36E4FBD1" box="[797,1008,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">L. (H.) helobius</emphasis>
Ma &amp; Yu
</taxonomicName>
, but the differences in arrangement of setae on clypeus, sensory pit of palpomere III, mandible with 
<number id="3DFA2485FFB5FFD9FBFF716A3164FBB7" box="[1106,1136,1085,1111]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" value="12.0">12</number>
teeth, wing with pale or brown stigma and anterior veins, ill developed radial cell, elongate gonocoxite, short gonostylus with setae, nipple-like aedaegus, parameres with truncated base and subapical fang-like structure justify its distinction as a new species of 
<emphasis id="B946EAB0FFB5FFD9FEF271FA37B1FB26" box="[351,677,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FEF271FA34E1FB26" box="[351,501,1197,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Leptoconops</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C324D21FFB5FFD9FDA071FA3788FB26" authority="Kieffer, 1918" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1918" box="[525,668,1197,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Holoconops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Holoconops</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3257632FFB5FFD9FD4171FA3638FB27" box="[748,812,1197,1223]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
